cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LO, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and finite automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses operations on numeration systems.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses formal power series to characterize recognizable sets of integers.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the regular language L.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of multiplication in certain numeration systems.
